For existing accounts, deposit values for each period represent a total of all of the deposits in the account or portfolio within that same period. Initial deposits for new accounts are
included in the Beginning Balance in the month following the initial deposit (e.g., a deposit made on January 15 would be captured in the Beginning Balance in February). For accounts
opened prior to July 1, 2020, the initial deposit is based on the market value at the beginning of the first full month in cases where the actual amount deposited in the account is
unavailable for reporting. The purchase of foreign currency is treated as a withdrawal from the account, and the sale of foreign currency is treated as a deposit into the account.
Additionally, foreign currency positions are excluded from the total market value and dividends paid in foreign currencies are not reflected in the dividend income. The net advisory

does not include any additional fees and credits or fees associated with the underlying investments held in your account. If you paid your Quarterly Advisory Fee by check or from
funds outside your account, payment is shown as Deposits in Total Deposits/Withdrawals. On summary view, account balance and income details reflect values from the start of the
period specified through the previous day's close of business. Accrued interest and accrued dividends represent income to be paid as of the end of the time period represented. Once

shown. Interest and dividends for each period are shown. Market Change represents the change in your account due to investment activity, exclusive of interest, dividends, deposits,
and withdrawals. Please note we do not record transactions of deposits and withdrawals, of the same amount, on the same day, within the same account in this experience. To view
